OL,5, The energy price crisis caused the     
OL,6, sharpest increase in UK absolute       
OL,7, poverty in 30 years, new figures show. 
OL,9,FSteep prices rises, following Russia's 
OL,10,Finvasion of Ukraine, meant hundreds of 
OL,11,Fthousands more people fell into        
OL,12,Fabsolute poverty.                      
OL,14,FThe figure jumped to 12 million in     
OL,15,F2022-2023, a rise of 600,000.          
OL,17,FThis means the rate of absolute poverty
OL,18,Fin the UK now stands at 18% - a rise of
OL,19,F0.78 percentage points.                
